// Proving-gate fixture (leak fix): CONSTRUCT-AND-DROP BEFORE FIRST `.next()`.
//
// Construction pre-runs the generator body to its FIRST `yield`, which MOVES the
// owned "first-A" string into the companion out-slot with the value UN-consumed.
// The generator binding is then dropped at scope exit WITHOUT any `.next()`, so
// the companion is that string's sole owner. The scope-exit destroy must
// typed-drop the pending out value exactly once (no leak under LSan, no
// double-free under ASan) — before the fix this string leaked.
//
// Observable behaviour: the body runs to (and stops at) its first yield during
// construction, so "gen:first" prints; "gen:second" never prints (the body is
// suspended before it and is never resumed). "done" prints after the drop.
fn main() {
    let g = gen {
        println("gen:first");
        yield "first" + "-A";
        println("gen:second");
        yield "second" + "-B";
    };
    println("done");
}
